# Mcp Dev Tools rules

## Development Standards
- **Developing:** When starting with a new feature or a bug fix, create a branch first with prefix feat/ for feature and fix/ for bugfix.
- **Editing:** When editing files, before you save and close, make sure to check that you have not left any "++++ REMOVE" lines behind when you're done. 
- **Editing:** When your're done with edits run linter on edited files.
- **Tasks:** When a task is complete pause to ask the user if there is a need for review. You may do git commits but not git push and not PR unless specifically told to do so without permission. Even if you are on YOLO mode you will wait for permission unless specifically git push and/or PR is permitted explicitly.
- **Git:** When creating a Pull Request for an existing GitHub issue, always include the phrase 'Closes #issue_number' in the PR description to ensure the issue is automatically closed upon merge.

